Rating: 3
I'd like to respond to the cook who asked about making panna cotta with agar agar instead of gelatin. After MANY attempts at this, I finally got the amounts right (first few attempts resulted in hockey puck texture!). In place of the gelatin, use just under a teaspoon agar powder. Whisk it with all the other (cold) ingredients in a pot, allow it to dissolve for 10 minutes, bring to a boil while stirring occasionally, pour immediately into ramekins. Allow it to cool at room temp for about 10 minutes then refrigerate. Will set completely within a half hour. Silky smooth and delicious!

Rating: 4
This dessert was attractive as well as delicious. I prepared it in martini glasses and the layers of colour - caramel, white and strawberry made a pretty presentation. Since I am not very good with gelatine, it was safer. To reduce the fat, I reduced the cream by 1/3 and substituted milk. Next time, I would reduce the amount of sugar in the recipe as others have indicated they have done. Truly a yummy dessert.

