Rating: 3
Excellent recipe. However the directions need to specify the following: slowly add the warm cream mixture to the buttermilk whisking constantly to prevent curdling. When I first made the recipe, I added the cool buttermilk to the warm cream causing the mixture to curdle. This is a very sweet desert. I used only 3 tablespoons of granulated sugar in the cream mixture when I prepared it a second time and found the it just right with the carmelized sugar.